Key Responsibilities:

Accounting & Finance Operations

Manage day-to-day accounting activities including AP, AR, GL, bank reconciliations.
Ensure accurate bookkeeping and timely month-end and year-end closing.
Handle project-wise accounting, cost allocation, and expense tagging.
Conduct periodic credit reviews of existing customers to assess creditworthiness and exposure.
Approve credit limits and credit terms for new customers in coordination with sales and management, ensuring adherence to company credit policy and risk controls.
Compliance & Statutory

Ensure compliance with GST, TDS, Income Tax, PF, ESI, and other statutory requirements.
Coordinate with auditors for internal, statutory, and tax audits.
Manage filings, returns, assessments, and notices.
Cash Flow & Collections

Monitor and manage cash flow planning and forecasting
Track receivables, ageing reports, and ensure timely collections from customers
Coordinate with sales and project teams to resolve billing and collection issues
Ensure optimal working capital management
Financial Reporting & MIS

Prepare monthly, quarterly, and annual MIS reports.
Track revenue, margins, expenses, and project profitability.
Support management with financial analysis and budgeting inputs.

Coordination & Controls

Work closely with Sales, Projects, and Operations teams for financial accuracy.
Ensure adherence to internal financial controls and SOPs.
Support leadership in financial planning and decision-making.
