9
1. Process Design, Revenue Assurance & Financial Controls
• Lead design and adherence of robust financial processes ensuring reconciliation of high-volume digital transactions.
• Build automated reconciliation systems to detect revenue leakages and ensure real-time accuracy across wallets, cards, and
UPI transactions.
• Strengthening internal control mechanisms to safeguard and prevent fraud.
• Drive process standardization, automation, and audit-readiness across finance operations.
2. Financial Planning & Analysis (FP&A)
• Lead annual operating plans (AOP), forecasting, and performance tracking.
• Partner with business heads to monitor key metrics- revenue, margins, and cost drivers enabling data-backed decision-making.
• Build advanced financial models for scenario planning and profitability analysis.
• Drive actionable insights through dashboards and predictive analytics.
• Establish capital allocation frameworks ensuring optimal use of funds between growth, innovation, and compliance.
• Collaborate with product teams to drive product innovation and enhancement
3. Profitability & Cost Optimization
• Track unit economics and product-level profitability.
• Identify and drive cost optimization initiatives across marketing, technology, operations, and credit portfolios.
• Implement automation and AI-driven tools for efficiency improvement and cost control.
4. Treasury & Liquidity Management
• Manage cash flow, working capital, and liquidity to support growth and regulatory requirements.
• Optimize capital allocation and fund utilization for maximum ROI.
5. Compliance & Governance
• Ensure adherence to RBI, SEBI, and other financial regulations.
• Manage audit readiness and statutory compliance across all entities and licenses.
• Partner with Legal and Compliance for timely reporting and governance.
6. Corporate Strategy & Investor Relations
• Support fundraising initiatives, M&A evaluation, and investor communications as needed.
7. Leadership & Capability Building
• Build a future-ready finance team with expertise in fintech analytics, automation, and regulatory reporting.
• Champion a culture of accountability and ethical finance practices.
• Lead digital transformation within finance — e.g., AI-driven reconciliation, predictive analytics, etc
